						<summary>

						<p>This may be assigned to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi> It is incomplete and records some gift (probably of gold) made by one <hi rend="bold">Ariñjigai Āḻi••••</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Peruṅkūṟṟakkuḍi</hi> in [Kū]ḍalūr-nāḍu for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tirumūlaṭṭānattu-Paramēśvara a Tirunalakkuṉṟam in Kuṉṟiyūr-nāḍu (No. 74, <hi rend="italic">Pud. Ins.</hi> Texts).</p>						

